The paper discusses a technique for estimating selectivity in query optimization, which is a core problem in database systems. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a machine learning-based approach using mixture models, which falls under the scope of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves optimization algorithms, which is a topic in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
